  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through multiple complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate and retrievable\n\nLegal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most involve intentionally hiding the origins of money from illegal activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other criminal enterprises.",
